oomberg.\n15 Million Tons\nAmyris operates a small farnesene production plant in Sao Paulo state and is building facilities at mills owned by Sao Martinho SA (SMTO3) and Paraiso Bioenergia SA that will enable it to process up to 3 million tons of cane, he said.\nThe company has formed agreements with Cosan Ltd. (CZZ) , Bunge Ltd. (BG) and Guarani SA and will have access to about 15 million tons of cane-crushing capacity by 2015, he said.\nAmyris plans to produce as much as 50 million liters (13.2 million gallons) of farnesene next year from facilities around the world, he said.\n\u201cWe don\u2019t just make fuel for the car from it, but the tires and the dashboard,\u201d he said.\nTo contact the reporter on this story: Stephan Nielsen in Sao Paulo at snielsen8@bloomberg.net\nTo contact the editor responsible for this story: Will Wade at wwade4@bloomberg.net\nMore News:\n", "update_time": "2012-10-22 14:47:29", "post_time": "2011-10-20 14:03:13", "author": "Stephan Nielsen", "url": "http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/amyris-eth-bioenergia-to-make-fuel-precursor-in-brazil.html", "title": "Amyris, ETH Bioenergia to Make Fuel Precursor in Brazil", "post_date": "2011-10-20", "source": "Bloomberg News", "stock_index": "IBOV", "embers_id": "643959cbc1eebcf359330cd0da9c5d53b954c771"}, {"content": "Highbridge Capital Management Holdings in 2nd Quarter: 13F Alert\nBy Chris Cappucci - 2011-08-15T14:42:11Z\nThe following is an analysis of Highbridge Capital Management LLC as of June 30, according to a filing with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission on 08/15/2011.\nTop Positions by Market Value  Company Name                 Ticker      Market Value      Current     Change                                             (USD $)       Position  In Position Arcos Dorados Holdings Inc-A ARCO US      410,218,574   19,450,857   19,450,857 Cosan Ltd-Class A Shares     CZZ US       407,632,483   33,167,818   -1,131,572 Mosaic Co/The                MOS US       331,871,175    